Russia’s RTS Futures Index Falls 0.1% at Start of Trading

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-07-01T15:10:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/russia-s-rts-futures-index-falls-0-1-at-start-of-trading.html
Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
expiring in September fell 0.1 percent at 11:01 a.m. in  New
York .  Contracts on OAO Lukoil, the second-biggest oil producer,
dropped 0.1 percent. Contracts on OAO Gazprom, the natural-gas
export monopoly, slid 0.1 percent. Contracts on OAO Sberbank,
Russia’s largest lender, were little changed.  The Market Vectors Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that
holds Russian shares, gained 1 percent.  -- Editors: Alex Nicholson, Stephen Kirkland  To contact the reporter on this story:
